Title: Fossil Mighty Mouse watch with FREE Mickey Mouse watch! NO RESERVE!
Description: Here's a fun, little combination. Two famous cartoon mouse watches for the price of one. I suppose the Mighty Mouse watch is the more valuable of the two. It is after all a limited edition. Mine is 809 of 15,000 made by Fossil in 1994. It is model number LI-1275. I've seen them here on eBay selling, or attempting to sell, for about $70 with all the original box and papers. I'm simply offering the watch itself and a mousey companion for free: an old school Mickey watch made by Lorus which is a budget brand under the Seiko corporate umbrella. Both watches' straps have been replaced and Mickey's battery will need replacing. But Mighty Mouse is running mightily. Mighty's strap is a cordovan leather. Looks great with the red highlights on the face of the watch. Mighty's case is 35mm in diameter, Mickey's a mere 30mm. So these watches are small by today's standard for a man but they are entirely appropriate for a woman, child or a self-assured, whimsical, watch-collecting type o'guy. I am really just trying to clear out some inventory while monetizing some of my beloved, old watches. So NO RESERVE. Starting bid outrageously low and free shipping. What more could you ask for? Oh, you'd like a free Mickey Mouse watch? Check.
ConditionDescription: Good condition on both watches. Both excellent time keepers in good-to-go condition.
